The paper deals with a class of stochastic hybrid systems, which involve both continuous and discrete dynamics. This is a topic that is relevant to several areas of computer science, including control theory (cs.SY), modeling and simulation (cs.MS), data science (cs.DS), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and machine learning (cs.LG). The specific focus on linear piecewise deterministic Markov processes and families of random discrete events suggests that cs.SY and cs.MS are the most likely categories, followed by cs.DS, cs.NA, and cs.LG.
